OL,3,CStreeting to 'look at' mental capacity
OL,4,Claw change after murder of autistic man
OL,6,FHowever, research has found that such
OL,7,Fassessments are either not carried out
OL,8,Fenough or are not carried out
OL,9,Feffectively in particular on autistic
OL,10,Fpeople, adults with learning
OL,11,Fdisabilities or those with mental
OL,12,Fhealth issues, such as bipolar.
OL,14,FTheir insistence that they can cope is
OL,15,Foften taken at face value without
OL,16,Fconsidering their past history and
OL,17,Frelatives' concerns. This means that -
OL,18,Fas in Christopher Laskaris' case -
OL,19,Fthey are left without the support they
OL,20,Fneed.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G9/13
